Class BTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>

java.lang.Object
BTree<E>
Type Parameters:
E - This is type of the data for the BTree.
All Implemented Interfaces:
SearchTree<E>
public class BTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements SearchTree<E>
Author:
Koffman and Wolfgang An implementation of the B-tree. A B-tree is a search tree in which each node contains n data items where n is between (order-1)/2 and order-1. (For the root, n may be between 1 and order-1) Each node not a leaf has n+1 children. The tree is always balanced in that all leaves are on the same level, i.e., the length of the path from the root to a leaf is constant.
